data.title: Initial Agreement Reached In Greece Power-Sharing
data.meta_description: Prime Minister George Papandreou has made clear he will not head the interim government, the president's office said. The announcement caps a week of drama sparked by Papandreou's announcement he was taking the European debt deal to a referendum. He withdrew the plan after intense opposition from European leaders and his own lawmakers.
